cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper deals with machine translation, specifically addressing the challenge of zero pronoun translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a neural MT model that jointly learns to predict and translate zero pronouns, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) also likely categories. The use of hierarchical neural networks suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision, indicating cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a less likely but still possible category.
